y youths at Makinde area of Oshodi, Lagos, yesterday, staged a protest over the death of one of them, Rafiu Adeniji, who was allegedly shot dead by a policeman attached to Agege area on Sunday. October 8, 2013 In "News" Tragedy struck Wednesday, at Elebele in the outskirts of Yenagoa, the Bayelsa State capital when a trigger happy cop shot dead two persons, an Okada rider and his passenger for allegedly refusing to part with gratification at a chekpoint. November 24, 2010 In "News" AWKA- VIOLENT protest sparked off in Onitsha, the commercial city of Anambra State Thursday, over the killing of a commercial bus driver simply identified as Edwin by a trigger happy policeman for failing to part with N50 tip. February 9, 2012 In "News"